article.headline: High Point 94, Covenant 67
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid led all players with a career-best 32 points and 17 rebounds as High Point beat Covenant 94-67 on Wednesday. Reid hit 15-of-20 field goal attempts, scoring 22 points and grabbing 11 rebounds in the second half. Landon Quick added 13 points and Jerald Minnis had 10 for the Panthers (2-2), and Mike Jefferson finished with 12 assists. Quick, Jefferson, Gene Harris and Troy Bowen each scored 3-pointers for High Point, which led 35-29 at the half. High Point had a double-digit lead two minutes into the second half and led the rest of the game. The Panthers shot 54.7 percent from the field, and held the Scots (1-4) to 29 percent. Caleb Skogen led Covenant with 14 points and brother Jacob Skogen added 11.
